00:21:44.660 --> 00:21:54.120
A subject that isn't really present on the political stage and in the information world is water.

00:21:54.120 --> 00:22:03.500
I get back to it quite often because I think that the cycle of water is one of the great stakes for human societies since the beginning.

00:22:03.500 --> 00:22:06.640
So we can still believe that because we have running water then it's not a problem anymore.

00:22:06.640 --> 00:22:10.980
But it's still a problem because we need to do with water in tubes and what water?

00:22:10.980 --> 00:22:17.020
So, even before we talk about water valve and individual access to water,

00:22:17.020 --> 00:22:26.000
we need to ask ourselves about water itself, because the humonguous human presence on the surface of the earth

00:22:26.000 --> 00:22:31.660
produces all sort of pollution, we already talked about pesticides and all that,

00:22:31.660 --> 00:22:35.600
and there is also pollutions that are linked to the human presence itself,

00:22:35.600 --> 00:22:40.020
that is to say to the fact that we're human beings, and human beings

00:22:40.020 --> 00:22:48.320
well they spread everywhere fecal matter and urine and everything, and all that goes to the ground

00:22:48.320 --> 00:22:54.800
because there is a lot of places where it's not picked up by anybody, and from here, it gets into water.

00:22:54.820 --> 00:23:04.520
And then the World Health Organization finds out that there are 2 billion people

00:23:04.520 --> 00:23:08.960
that drink water infested by fecal matter.

00:23:08.960 --> 00:23:16.380
2 billion, it's roughly the equivalent of the total population of the planet

00:23:16.380 --> 00:23:24.760
in the 50's of the previous century, so that you can see how much it represent.

00:23:24.760 --> 00:23:34.200
It's a huge number of people and every year 500 000 persons die

00:23:34.200 --> 00:23:44.820
because of diarrhea, epidemics that spread because of the fact that we drink water that is polluted by fecal matter.

00:23:44.820 --> 00:23:53.500
So it's a gigantic problem that would cost nothing to solve -  or almost nothing -

00:23:53.500 --> 00:23:58.300
if the Monetary Fund, the World Bank, all the people that have money

00:23:58.300 --> 00:24:08.020
got interested in anything else than trading of goods and the debts of countries.

00:24:08.020 --> 00:24:17.100
Something needs to be done here and I think that we, once we get to power, we'll have a water policy

00:24:17.100 --> 00:24:28.840
but a water policy from its collection, its treatment, its delivery,

00:24:28.840 --> 00:24:36.760
its re-treatment once it's been used and about the way to put all this at the service of the human ensemble

00:24:36.760 --> 00:24:43.500
of agriculture, of human beings, of animals, well, of all of those that have to do with the cycle of water;

00:24:43.500 --> 00:24:51.960
The cycle of water, it's the fundamental cycle of life itself. You're composed of 85% of water and it's just this was.

00:24:51.960 --> 00:25:00.440
Water is the fundamental matter of the living, so to solve a problem of this nature investments are needed

00:25:00.440 --> 00:25:05.240
and those are good investments because they guarantee the good health of the people

00:25:05.240 --> 00:25:10.980
in the same time as a water circulation that makes their life infinitely less painful

00:25:10.980 --> 00:25:16.940
and that's also a lot of jobs, so we find in this business

00:25:16.940 --> 00:25:23.420
the needs, the necessities of cooperation, because we need to give to countries that needs

00:25:23.420 --> 00:25:31.620
technics that allows them to collect, clean and redistribute water and we now how to do all of this, us french,

00:25:31.620 --> 00:25:36.240
be it by private companies or by the state.

00:25:36.240 --> 00:25:42.180
It isn't up to me to go and quote the private companies that I have been in conflict with in France

00:25:42.180 --> 00:25:48.300
because their role isn't as bright as some might tell you, but here are some ideas for the future

00:25:48.300 --> 00:25:52.080
and it pleases me to see that as we mentionned and as we explained in our programs

00:25:52.080 --> 00:25:58.060
some Development NGOs - at least 5 of them -

00:25:58.060 --> 00:26:05.180
said that our program was the program best fit to these problems and questions that are being raised by the co-development

00:26:05.180 --> 00:26:10.500
term that was very popular ten years ago and a lot less now

00:26:10.500 --> 00:26:15.380
because those who wrapped themselves in this word didn't do anything

00:26:15.380 --> 00:26:19.980
or things that are deplorable since then. But I'll come back to it, I believe in co-development

00:26:19.980 --> 00:26:26.540
everytime a country goes better, the others around goes better, that's what I believe in.

00:26:26.540 --> 00:26:31.560
